    "description": "&quot;A Mazing Cheesesnake&quot; caters to those who enjoy a customized &amp;  slightly more challenging maze experience. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n  3 difficulties, 100 mazes per difficulty, all of which can be played forward or reversed. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n====================  4 Maze Modes ====================<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCasual mode for just getting to the finish, and an option to add food to gather first.<br />\r\nTimed mode to encourage you find the shortest path before starting your motion.<br />\r\nExplorer mode is a fully covered maze only seeing the area around the cheesenake.<br />\r\nHunter mode is also covered, but keeps uncovered where the cheesesnake has been.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith 300 mazes and four distinct ways to play each one, it provides ample replay value for your daily puzzle-solving brain stimulation. Solving mazes is a beneficial exercise for the brain, enhancing short-term memory, mental focus, and concentration.  Not only good for kids development, but also great for us older ones to help keep ours sharp.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nA maze a day helps keep the brain engaged!",
